                <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="48" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by Thoerax[/i]
[br]Clerics --
Will CH and fast heal you if you are below 50% health and/or getting beat on.

Shamans --
Will slow mobs (altho not always)

Necros --
Blow as pets.  They don't get Funeral Pyre or any new nukes so its (Darkness, Root, Pyro, and ToN)

Enchanters --
Tash, Root, DD, (am told they cripple but don't know the message for cripple)

Pallies --
Do LoH if they are getting really beat on so possible usefull if your blocking a nasty mob for a few secs.

Warriors --
BLOW

Monks --
BLOW

Rogues --
Do BS but I havn't seen it above 200

SK's --
Harm Touch and for some reason DW like other melee.

Wizzies --
Sunstrike, root, snare, Lure DD's

Mages --
Best for damage imo.  Just mala and DD (altho not for as much as wizzie per spell)

Ranger --
Havn't tested much but the one I did wake tryed some snare, root, and same capped melee. (also was useing a bow when I woke and it meleed still)

Bard --
Didn't see it sing a single thing just meleed same as other non-casters

----

Now for some myth dispelling.
#1
They don't proc the weapons that the corpse is useing.  It simple hits like unequiped mobs.

#2
They cast off the NPC table so it doesn't matter if its a lvl 65 wizzie with all spells or a lvl 65 wizzie with only lvl 1 root memed.. they will both sunstrike and lure.

#3
They don't have any inate procs (i.e. dragon breath, AE stuns, or whatever else the mob is doing before it dies) It does however proc vampiric embrace (like all our pets)

#4
There seems to be a fixed hp value on any mobe you wake.  I've woken lvl 18 mobs that seemed to have the same 3-8k the others do.

-thoerax
rodcet nife


